Bills passed by a simple majority are sent to the mayor -LRB- the President of Warsaw -RRB- , who may sign them into law .
Generally , in Poland , the mayors of bigger cities are called presidents -- i.e. such cities , which have over 100,000 people or these , where already was president before 1990 .
Between 1975 and 1990 the Warsaw Presidents was simultaneously the Warsaw Voivode .
Since 2002 the President of Warsaw is elected by all of the citizens of Warsaw .
Warsaw 's ever-growing business community has been noticed globally , regionally , and nationally .
MasterCard Emerging Market Index has noted Warsaw 's economic strength and commercial center .
