Warsaw leads the region of East-Central Europe in foreign investment and in 2006 , GDP growth met expectations with a level of 6.1 % .
It also has one of the fastest growing economies , with GDP growth at 6.5 percent in 2007 and 6.1 percent in the first quarter of 2008 .
