The embargo caused an oil crisis , or `` shock '' , with many short - and long-term effects on global politics and the global economy .
The crisis had a major impact on international relations and created a rift within NATO .
Arab oil producers linked any future policy changes to peace between the belligerents .
To address this , the Nixon Administration began multilateral negotiations with the combatants .
Shortly thereafter , Britain followed , floating the pound sterling .
The other industrialized nations followed suit with their respective currencies .
The result was a depreciation of the dollar and other industrialized nations ' currencies .
This contributed to the `` Oil Shock '' .
OPEC ministers had not developed institutional mechanisms to update prices in sync with changing market conditions , so their real incomes lagged .
Weeks later , the Shah of Iran said in an interview : `` Of course -LSB- the price of oil -RSB- is going to rise ... Certainly !
And how !
... You 've -LSB- Western nations -RSB- increased the price of the wheat you sell us by 300 percent , and the same for sugar and cement ... You buy our crude oil and sell it back to us , refined as petrochemicals , at a hundred times the price you 've paid us ... It 's only fair that , from now on , you should pay more for oil .
