Before the introduction of X. 25 in 1973 , about twenty different network technologies had been developed .
In the datagram system , the hosts have the responsibility to ensure orderly delivery of packets .
This results in a simpler host interface with less functionality than in the datagram model .
The X. 25 protocol suite uses this network type .
It was the primary protocol used by Apple devices through the 1980s and 90s .
First demonstrated in 1973 , it was developed to explore alternatives to the early ARPANET design and to support network research generally .
It evolved into one of the first peer-to-peer network architectures , thus transforming DEC into a networking powerhouse in the 1980s .
The DECnet protocols were designed entirely by Digital Equipment Corporation .
