In October 1972 connections to the CDC mainframe at Michigan State University in East Lansing completed the triad .
All of this set the stage for Merit 's role in the NSFNET project starting in the mid-1980s .
He had tried to interest AT&T in buying the technology , but the monopoly 's reaction was that this was incompatible with their future .
Bolt , Beranack and Newman -LRB- BBN -RRB- provided the financing .
Telenet designed these protocols and helped standardize them in the CCITT .
Telenet was incorporated in 1973 and started operations in 1975 .
It went public in 1979 and was then sold to GTE .
Tymnet was also connected to dozens of other public networks in the U.S. and internationally via X. 25/X .75 gateways .
