Another employee suggested the name . -RRB-
There were two kinds of X. 25 networks .
Some such as DATAPAC and TRANSPAC were initially implemented with an X. 25 external interface .
Some older networks such as TELENET and TYMNET were modified to provide a X. 25 host interface in addition to older host connection schemes .
Northern Telecom sold several DATAPAC clones to foreign PTTs including the Deutsche Bundespost .
X. 75 and X. 121 allowed the interconnection of national X. 25 networks .
