The Victorian industrial revolution brought industrial structures that included the 2 1⁄2 - mile -LRB- 4.0 km -RRB- Victoria Tunnelling , built in 1842 , which provided underground wagon ways to the staithes .
On 3 February 1879 , Mosley Street in the city , was the first public road in the world to be lit up by the incandescent lightbulb .
In 1882 , Newcastle became the seat of an Anglican diocese , with St. Nicholas ' Church becoming its cathedral .
