Malindi has traditionally been a friendly port city for foreign powers .
In 1414 , the Chinese trader and explorer Zheng He representing the Ming Dynasty visited the East African coast on one of his last ` treasure voyages ' .
Malindi authorities welcomed the Portuguese explorer Vasco da Gama in 1498 .
