The connection to prime numbers is that it essentially says that the primes are as regularly distributed as possible .
This hypothesis is generally believed to be correct .
In particular , the simplest assumption is that primes should have no significant irregularities without good reason .
In addition to the Riemann hypothesis , many more conjectures revolving about primes have been posed .
Also , any even integer can be written as the sum of six primes .
The branch of number theory studying such questions is called additive number theory .
A third type of conjectures concerns aspects of the distribution of primes .
Legendre 's conjecture states that there is a prime number between n2 and -LRB- n + 1 -RRB- 2 for every positive integer n .
It is implied by the stronger Cramér 's conjecture .
Giuga 's conjecture says that this equation is also a sufficient condition for p to be prime .
