Its prime elements are known as Gaussian primes .
Not every prime -LRB- in Z -RRB- is a Gaussian prime : in the bigger ring Z -LSB- i -RSB- , 2 factors into the product of the two Gaussian primes -LRB- 1 + i -RRB- and -LRB- 1 − i -RRB- .
Arithmetic geometry also benefits from this notion , and many concepts exist in both geometry and number theory .
Such ramification questions occur even in number-theoretic questions solely concerned with integers .
These are essentially all possible ways to complete Q , by Ostrowski 's theorem .
Prime numbers have influenced many artists and writers .
