The United Methodist Church upholds the sanctity of human life both of the child and the mother .
As a result , the church is `` reluctant to affirm abortion as an acceptable practice , '' and condemns the use of late-term or partial birth abortion except as a medical necessity .
The denomination as a whole is committed to `` assist -LSB- ing -RSB- the ministry of crisis pregnancy centers and pregnancy resource centers that compassionately help women find feasible alternatives to abortion . ''
In continuity with past Christian teaching , we recognize tragic conflicts of life with life that may justify abortion , and in such cases we support the legal option of abortion under proper medical procedures . ''
The church cautions that `` Governmental laws and regulations do not provide all the guidance required by the informed Christian conscience . ''
