Given current trends in the UMC -- with overseas churches growing , especially in Africa , and U.S. churches collectively losing about 1,000 members a week -- it has been estimated that Africans will make up at least 30 % of the delegates at the 2012 General Conference , and it is also possible that 40 % of the delegates will be from outside the U.S. .
One Congolese bishop has estimated that typical Sunday attendance of the UMC is higher in his country than in the entire United States .
